Title: GitHub Explorer

Description:
A web application designed to explore GitHub repositories, users, and organizations. This project was developed during my internship to enhance my skills in front-end development, API integration, and JavaScript programming.

Features
User and Repository Search:

Implemented a search functionality to allow users to find GitHub users and repositories quickly.
Utilized the GitHub API to fetch and display user profiles and repository details dynamically.
Detailed Repository View:

Displayed detailed information about repositories including the description, star count, forks, and programming language.
Implemented navigation to view individual repositories with a clean and intuitive interface.
User Profile View:

Displayed comprehensive user profiles including avatar, bio, repositories, followers, and following count.
Enabled navigation to user profiles directly from the search results.
Responsive Design:

Ensured the application is fully responsive, providing an optimal viewing experience across various devices including desktops, tablets, and mobile phones.
Used CSS media queries to adapt the layout and elements dynamically based on screen size.
Interactive User Interface:

Designed a user-friendly and interactive interface using modern web technologies.
Implemented loading indicators and error handling to improve user experience.
API Integration:

Integrated with the GitHub REST API to fetch real-time data.
Handled API rate limiting and optimized the number of API calls to ensure efficient data retrieval.
